"title": "8620: prayer, practicalities of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8620",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture commends a life of prayer, characterised by simplicity of expression, sincerity of heart and trust in the promises of God.  It gives guidance on how, when and where to pray.</p>\n<h2>Scripture stresses the importance of prayer</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:16-1Thess5:18\">1TH 5:16–5:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:3-Acts6:4\">ACT 6:3–6:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:12\">ROM 12:12</a></p>\n<h2>Judgment comes on those who do not pray</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps79:6\">PSA 79:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps53:4\">PSA 53:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:21\">JER 10:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zeph1:4-Zeph1:6\">ZEP 1:4–1:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:2\">JAS 4:2</a></p>\n<h2>Prayers should be expressed simply</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:7-Matt6:8\">MAT 6:7–6:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:1-Eccl5:3\">ECC 5:1–5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:9-Luke18:14\">LUK 18:9–18:14</a></p>\n<h2>Prayer should not be ostentatious</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:5-Matt6:6\">MAT 6:5–6:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:23\">MAT 14:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:46\">MRK 6:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:16\">LUK 5:16</a></p>\n<h2>Physical positions for prayer</h2>\n<h3>Sitting while praying</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:18\">2SA 7:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:26\">JDG 20:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:4\">NEH 1:4</a></p>\n<h3>Kneeling while praying</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:41\">LUK 22:41</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:54\">1KI 8:54</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:13\">2CH 6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:5\">EZR 9:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:40\">ACT 9:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:5\">ACT 21:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:14\">EPH 3:14</a></p>\n<h3>Standing while praying</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:22\">1KI 8:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:26\">1SA 1:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:25\">MRK 11:25</a></p>\n<h3>Lying prostrate while praying</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:18\">2CH 20:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:52\">GEN 24:52</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:6\">NUM 20:6</a></p>\n<h3>Praying with arms outstretched</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:29\">EXO 9:29</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:15\">ISA 1:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:54\">1KI 8:54</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr6:13\">2CH 6:13</a></p>\n<h3>Praying with hands raised</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:8\">1TI 2:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:29\">EXO 9:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:22\">1KI 8:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:54\">1KI 8:54</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps63:4\">PSA 63:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps77:1-Ps77:2\">PSA 77:1–77:2</a></p>\n<h2>Prayer can be offered at any time</h2>\n<h3>Praying several times a day</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:10\">DAN 6:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps55:17\">PSA 55:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:1\">PSA 88:1</a></p>\n<h3>Praying early in the morning</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:35\">MRK 1:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:3\">PSA 5:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:147\">PSA 119:147</a></p>\n<h3>Praying all night</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:12\">LUK 6:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:11\">1SA 15:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:37\">LUK 2:37</a></p>\n<h2>Prayer is not confined to any single place</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:21-John4:24\">JHN 4:21–4:24</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Praying inside a building</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:10\">DAN 6:10</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:6\">MAT 6:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:28-1Kgs8:30\">1KI 8:28–8:30</a></p>\n<h3>Praying outside a building</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:35\">MRK 1:35</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:16\">LUK 5:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:9\">ACT 10:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:5\">ACT 21:5</a></p>\n<h2>Prayer may be accompanied by fasting</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:2-Acts13:3\">ACT 13:2–13:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:23\">EZR 8:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:4\">NEH 1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:13\">PSA 35:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:3\">DAN 9:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:37\">LUK 2:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:33\">LUK 5:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:23\">ACT 14:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:21\">MAT 17:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:29\">MRK 9:29</a></p>",
